{"cursor":"4028","size":15,"audio":[],"currentlang":"en","article":"\n\n{{Infobox UK legislation |short_title = Marine (Scotland) Act 2010 |parliament =\nScottish Parliament |long_title = An Act of the Scottish Parliament to make\nprovision in relation to functions and activities in the Scottish marine area,\nincluding provision about marine plans, licensing of marine activities, the\nprotection of the area and its wildlife including seals and regulation of sea\nfisheries; and for connected purposes. |year = 2010 |statute_book_chapter =\n|introduced_by = |territorial_extent = Scotland |royal_assent = 10 March 2010\n|commencement = |repeal_date = |amendments = |related_legislation =\n|repealing_legislation= |status = Current |original_text = |activeTextDocId =\n|legislation_history = |use_new_UK-LEG = }} On 10 March 2010, Scotland's Marine\nBill received Royal Assent, making it the\n[http://www.oqps.gov.uk/legislation/acts/acts2010/pdf/asp_20100005_en.pdf Marine\n(Scotland) Act 2010].\n\nThe Marine (Scotland) Act provides a framework which will help balance competing\ndemands on Scotland's seas. It introduces a duty to protect and enhance the\nmarine environment and includes measures to help boost economic investment and\ngrowth in areas such as marine renewables.\n\nThe main measures include:\n\n*[http://www.scotland.gov.uk/Topics/marine/seamanagement/marineact/marineplanni-\nng Marine planning]: a new statutory marine planning system to sustainably\nmanage the increasing, and often conflicting, demands on our seas *[http://www.-\nscotland.gov.uk/Topics/marine/seamanagement/marineact/marinelicensing Marine\nlicensing]: a simpler licensing system, minimising the number of licences\nrequired for development in the marine environment to cut bureaucracy and\nencourage economic investment\n\n*[http://www.scotland.gov.uk/Topics/marine/seamanagement/marineact/marineconser-\nvation Marine conservation]: improved marine nature and historic conservation\nwith new powers to protect and manage areas of importance for marine wildlife,\nhabitats and historic monuments\n* [http://www.scotland.gov.uk/Topics/marine/seamanagement/marineact/SealsSeal\n  conservation]: much improved protection for seals and a new comprehensive\n  licence system to ensure appropriate management when necessary *[http://www.s-\n  cotland.gov.uk/Topics/marine/seamanagement/marineact/marineenforcement\n  Enforcement]: a range of enhanced powers of marine conservation and licensing\n","linknr":141,"url":"Marine_(Scotland)_Act_2010","recorded":1375055893,"links":["/w/index.php?title=Marine_(Scotland)_Act_2010&action=edit","/w/index.php?title=Marine_(Scotland)_Act_2010&action=edit","//bits.wikimedia.org/favicon/wikipedia.ico","/w/opensearch_desc.php","//en.wikipedia.org/w/api.php?action=rsd","//creativecommons.org/licenses/by-sa/3.0/","/w/index.php?title=Special:RecentChanges&feed=atom","//bits.wikimedia.org/en.wikipedia.org/load.php?debug=false&lang=en&modules=ext.gadget.DRN-wizard%2CReferenceTooltips%2Ccharinsert%2Cteahouse%7Cext.rtlcite%2Cwikihiero%7Cext.uls.nojs%7Cmediawiki.legacy.commonPrint%2Cshared%7Cmw.PopUpMediaTransform%7Cskins.vector&only=styles&skin=vector&*","//bits.wikimedia.org/en.wikipedia.org/load.php?debug=false&lang=en&modules=site&only=styles&skin=vector&*","//bits.wikimedia.org/en.wikipedia.org/load.php?debug=false&lang=en&modules=startup&only=scripts&skin=vector&*","//bits.wikimedia.org/geoiplookup","//meta.wikimedia.org","#mw-navigation","#p-search","//upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/1/13/Royal_Coat_of_Arms_of_the_United_Kingdom_%28Government_in_Scotland%29.svg/140px-Royal_Coat_of_Arms_of_the_United_Kingdom_%28Government_in_Scotland%29.svg.png","/wiki/Scottish_Parliament","/wiki/Long_title","/wiki/Scotland","/wiki/Royal_Assent","http://www.oqps.gov.uk/legislation/acts/acts2010/pdf/asp_20100005_en.pdf","/wiki/Scotland%27s_seas","/wiki/Marine_environment","/wiki/Marine_renewables","http://www.scotland.gov.uk/Topics/marine/seamanagement/m